	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have a success rate of about 8% currently on all velious tailored items with a skill level in the mid 160s. I have spent greater than 6k plat for the 100 attempts that I have made and about 100 hours gathering components. This does not include the time that my fellow guildmates have spent gathering materials for me as well. In all the time we have spent in CS killing wyverns we have received over 150 hides but with over 20 drakes killed now, I have only seen 1 hide drop. The cobalt drake hide is a very rare drop. I am saving the one I have and any further one's that I manage to obtain until I can make 20 attempts all at once so as to have a decent chance of making just one belt. By the time you can succesfully make most of this stuff on a greater percentage chance, you will most likely have better gear in almost every slot. Tailoring is a skill that requires an immense amount of time and money to attain the highest levels of mastery and in the end does not pay for itself unless you are very lucky. With all that said, I am still a tailoring addict and will continue to tailor until my skill is maxed out at 200 since I specialized in JC. I have also made another character to specialize in tailoring. I guess I am insane to take to characters to 200 in tailoring but hey it's fun and one heck of a challenge.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Feb 19 18:24:40 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Shallinar Icefyre<br>Enchanter of Veeshan</td></tr>
