<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100803904850313></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100803904850313><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=skills.html?skill=10&mid=100803904850313>RE: Yew leaf</a> <a id=fs8 href=skills.html?skill=10&mid=100803904850313#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73409><span id=Scholar>Mistress ancarett</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>70 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 10th 9:50 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.40]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>First off, yew leaves can be foraged now by foraging classes/races so you might have some luck there.<br><br>Second, there are some maps that purport to show yew leaf spawn locations: search around the net. The one I remember seeing had them distributed in a rough, thick circle. Also, some people say that successful yew leaf foragers are running Show EQ utility on a second rig to help direct them to the exact loc of each leaf. Of course, Show EQ is illegal and running it can get you banned from EQ.<br><br>But, I have heard people say that tweaking your video settings and running with a pan/scan downwards to the ground can really help. Have you ever seen a ground spawn before? They look rather like lighter/brighter green diamonds against the ground. Once you know WHAT to look for and experiment with tweaking your settings to see these things, maybe you'll have better luck. I have had a lot of success finding groundspawns in many different zones, so I have a jump on others who haven't been looking as long.<br><br>And maybe you can find something for which your monk friend would trade that stack of yew leaves! Good luck!<br>&nbsp;<br>-- Yseulte/Ancarett<br>Veeshan Server</td></tr>
